1
00:00:41,867 --> 00:00:45,533
[This drama is fictional, and any resemblance
to real people or events is coincidental.]

2
00:00:46,300 --> 00:00:47,643
[Episode 3]

3
00:00:47,667 --> 00:00:50,709
My money, my choice!

4
00:00:50,733 --> 00:00:54,643
[Muchang Silver Town offers the best facilities!]
Come on, why object when I'm using my own money

5
00:00:54,667 --> 00:00:56,709
to develop my own land
and build my own building?

6
00:00:56,733 --> 00:01:03,076
This is exactly the kind of thing that
blocks Muchang's growth and development...

7
00:01:03,100 --> 00:01:04,876
Muchang strawberries are here!

8
00:01:04,900 --> 00:01:08,609
Korea's most delicious
strawberries from Muchang.

9
00:01:08,633 --> 00:01:10,376
[Muchang Strawberries]

10
00:01:10,400 --> 00:01:13,567
Hey, Jeon Dong Min. Will you turn that off?

11
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:19,776
You turn it off.

12
00:01:19,800 --> 00:01:21,576
This is right in front of a kindergarten.

13
00:01:21,600 --> 00:01:25,509
The kids are about to start class. You know
this is clearly disrupting their lesson, right?

14
00:01:25,533 --> 00:01:26,743
Whatever.

15
00:01:26,767 --> 00:01:30,909
And seriously, how many students
does this kindergarten even have?

16
00:01:30,933 --> 00:01:32,967
Stop getting in my way.

17
00:01:33,933 --> 00:01:37,000
Sorry about that, I'll continue.

18
00:01:38,567 --> 00:01:42,576
Our respected citizens of Muchang,

19
00:01:42,600 --> 00:01:44,300
during all this time...

20
00:01:58,400 --> 00:02:00,567
Oh, Jeong Woo! Perfect timing!

21
00:02:05,367 --> 00:02:08,209
Perfect timing? I came
because someone reported this, pal.

22
00:02:08,233 --> 00:02:10,643
That punk Jeon Dong Min hit me.

23
00:02:10,667 --> 00:02:12,309
I just aimed a kick at the megaphone.

24
00:02:12,333 --> 00:02:13,643
No, I actually got hit!

25
00:02:13,667 --> 00:02:15,843
Arrest him.

26
00:02:15,867 --> 00:02:17,076
What are you waiting for?

27
00:02:17,100 --> 00:02:18,143
Arrest him for what?

28
00:02:18,167 --> 00:02:20,743
Using a megaphone in front of
a kindergarten was also your fault.

29
00:02:20,767 --> 00:02:22,248
Huh?

30
00:02:22,272 --> 00:02:24,109
But there aren't any kids

31
00:02:24,133 --> 00:02:26,243
or teachers here today.

32
00:02:26,267 --> 00:02:28,309
It's basically a done deal
that the kindergarten's closing.

33
00:02:28,333 --> 00:02:29,476
Seriously, are you guys for real?

34
00:02:29,500 --> 00:02:31,343
We'll just pass through.

35
00:02:31,367 --> 00:02:33,676
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

36
00:02:33,700 --> 00:02:35,943
- Hello.
- Strawberry class kids.

37
00:02:35,967 --> 00:02:38,276
- What happens if you fight?
- It's bad!

38
00:02:38,300 --> 00:02:40,509
What was that? Louder!
What happens if you fight?

39
00:02:40,533 --> 00:02:42,109
- It's bad.
- It's bad.

40
00:02:42,133 --> 00:02:43,867
Exactly.

41
00:02:45,033 --> 00:02:47,700
Principal, can we talk for a moment?

42
00:02:48,600 --> 00:02:52,009
There are only nine kids here
and no homeroom teacher, right?

43
00:02:52,033 --> 00:02:54,143
Everyone, please wait just a moment.

44
00:02:54,167 --> 00:02:56,476
Yes, yes, ma'am.

45
00:02:56,500 --> 00:02:58,767
Thank you.

46
00:03:03,067 --> 00:03:07,009
This teacher will be arriving shortly.

47
00:03:07,033 --> 00:03:08,909
Can you see her?

48
00:03:08,933 --> 00:03:12,276
Dong Min, I need to teach the kids.
You go meet her instead.

49
00:03:12,300 --> 00:03:13,976
Oh my, she'll be here any minute now.

50
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:15,633
Go on.

51
00:03:17,433 --> 00:03:19,476
Iseon Women's University?

52
00:03:19,500 --> 00:03:21,409
Is this the teacher who's coming?

53
00:03:21,433 --> 00:03:23,100
Yes.

54
00:03:24,033 --> 00:03:25,976
Is this some kind of job scam?

55
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:27,909
Why would someone from
Iseon Women's University come to Muchang?

56
00:03:27,933 --> 00:03:31,576
Don introduced her.
That means she's reliable.

57
00:03:31,600 --> 00:03:33,309
I'm counting on you.

58
00:03:33,333 --> 00:03:35,067
I'll be watching.

59
00:03:38,867 --> 00:03:40,533
See?

60
00:03:43,300 --> 00:03:45,409
Hey! Jeon Dong Min, where are you going?

61
00:03:45,433 --> 00:03:47,643
Hey! You broke my megaphone.
Where are you going?

62
00:03:47,667 --> 00:03:49,743
Anyway, those gym rats are hopeless.

63
00:03:49,767 --> 00:03:51,967
Brains are useless but the body's

64
00:03:54,133 --> 00:03:55,733
pretty great.

65
00:03:56,533 --> 00:03:58,076
Hey, hey.

66
00:03:58,100 --> 00:04:03,009
No, I didn't mean it badly.
I meant you have a great physique...

67
00:04:03,033 --> 00:04:06,000
Here's for the megaphone, okay?

68
00:04:11,633 --> 00:04:14,133
I bought it for 5,000 won secondhand.

69
00:04:15,467 --> 00:04:17,109
- Let's go, follow me.
- Huh?

70
00:04:17,133 --> 00:04:18,209
Where are we going?

71
00:04:18,233 --> 00:04:20,800
We need to catch that punk Jeon Dong Min!

72
00:04:31,367 --> 00:04:33,567
Why's it suddenly raining?

73
00:04:39,133 --> 00:04:44,233
[Straight from farm, nationwide delivery]

74
00:05:15,267 --> 00:05:17,976
Uh, excuse me...

75
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:20,067
You're Ms. Bu Se Mi, aren't you?

76
00:05:22,933 --> 00:05:26,109
Madam, that guy is just an extra.

77
00:05:26,133 --> 00:05:28,876
Not a lead, not even a supporting role.

78
00:05:28,900 --> 00:05:31,376
Why is a guy who's not even
a supporting character here?

79
00:05:31,400 --> 00:05:34,400
Are you Ms. Bu Se Mi?

80
00:05:37,500 --> 00:05:39,167
Wait a minute...

81
00:05:40,633 --> 00:05:42,533
Excuse me, by any chance...

82
00:05:45,967 --> 00:05:47,643
Yes, that's right.

83
00:05:47,667 --> 00:05:49,600
I'm Bu Se Mi.

84
00:05:50,333 --> 00:05:52,209
Ah, yes.

85
00:05:52,233 --> 00:05:54,543
The principal of Iseon
Kindergarten sent me.

86
00:05:54,567 --> 00:05:56,267
Let's go.

87
00:06:03,933 --> 00:06:06,143
- Oh, let me carry that.
- No.

88
00:06:06,167 --> 00:06:09,767
No, I don't like anyone touching my things.

89
00:06:55,067 --> 00:06:57,033
It's really pouring.

90
00:06:59,867 --> 00:07:05,333
[Muchang Strawberries]

91
00:07:20,700 --> 00:07:23,800
The weather's been so unpredictable lately.

92
00:07:29,567 --> 00:07:31,167
Excuse me, Miss.

93
00:07:32,300 --> 00:07:36,000
Why are you wearing sunglasses?

94
00:07:37,233 --> 00:07:40,043
I'm very sensitive to UV rays.

95
00:07:40,067 --> 00:07:43,676
UV rays stay strong even on cloudy days.

96
00:07:43,700 --> 00:07:45,333
Ah, I see.

97
00:07:52,967 --> 00:07:54,568
But hey,

98
00:07:54,592 --> 00:07:58,533
have we really never met before?

99
00:08:00,567 --> 00:08:01,843
Not that I know of.

100
00:08:01,867 --> 00:08:04,167
Have you maybe seen me somewhere?

101
00:08:09,700 --> 00:08:10,876
'You're a Solo'.

102
00:08:10,900 --> 00:08:12,309
Oh, no.

103
00:08:12,333 --> 00:08:13,943
Well...

104
00:08:13,967 --> 00:08:15,767
You were on 'Couples to Hell', yes?

105
00:08:17,133 --> 00:08:18,867
Am I wrong?

106
00:08:20,433 --> 00:08:23,209
I just made a joke because it felt awkward.

107
00:08:23,233 --> 00:08:25,376
Let's just drive quietly.

108
00:08:25,400 --> 00:08:27,000
Okay.

109
00:08:36,967 --> 00:08:40,043
Didn't Chairman Ga
look like he has dementia?

110
00:08:40,067 --> 00:08:41,509
Dementia?

111
00:08:41,533 --> 00:08:42,609
Any hospital records?

112
00:08:42,633 --> 00:08:46,043
No records, but could we bribe
someone who worked in that house?

113
00:08:46,067 --> 00:08:48,943
In court, witnesses are critical
in cases like this.

114
00:08:48,967 --> 00:08:51,643
Seon Yeong, what about Butler Choi?

115
00:08:51,667 --> 00:08:54,309
And that strange caretaker?

116
00:08:54,333 --> 00:08:55,909
Start the lawsuit.

117
00:08:55,933 --> 00:08:59,143
We'll aim for annulment
of the marriage due to dementia.

118
00:08:59,167 --> 00:09:03,109
Attorney Kim, that's too
predictable and weak.

119
00:09:03,133 --> 00:09:04,733
Ah, you're right.

120
00:09:05,533 --> 00:09:08,809
By the way, Professor.
Kim Yeong Ran has a criminal record.

121
00:09:08,833 --> 00:09:12,300
She was sent to juvenile detention
for stealing sanitary pads as a child.

122
00:09:14,367 --> 00:09:16,267
Use that against her.

123
00:09:17,433 --> 00:09:22,267
A repeat offender who's been in and out
of juvenile for theft since minor years.

124
00:09:23,200 --> 00:09:27,367
Her mother too shuffled
through prisons for petty fraud.

125
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:31,643
A young woman with criminal records marries
a trillion-won conglomerate chairman

126
00:09:31,667 --> 00:09:34,543
and lives as his wife for a month.

127
00:09:34,567 --> 00:09:37,976
Yet the man transferred
enormous assets to her

128
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:40,933
as if he knew he was going to die.

129
00:09:42,400 --> 00:09:44,576
- Attorney Kim.
- Yes?

130
00:09:44,600 --> 00:09:45,876
Looks like we've got the framework.

131
00:09:45,900 --> 00:09:47,209
How about gaslighting?

132
00:09:47,233 --> 00:09:49,276
Brilliant, Professor.

133
00:09:49,300 --> 00:09:52,209
An elderly man with dementia manipulated
by a female bodyguard into marriage

134
00:09:52,233 --> 00:09:54,909
and handing over his fortune.

135
00:09:54,933 --> 00:09:56,443
- And...
- She gas lit Chairman Ga Sung Ho

136
00:09:56,467 --> 00:10:00,543
to the point of driving him to death.

137
00:10:00,567 --> 00:10:02,609
The widow, inheriting great wealth,

138
00:10:02,633 --> 00:10:06,976
disappeared after the funeral.

139
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:11,500
Dementia, criminal record,
gaslighting, assisted suicide...

140
00:10:14,100 --> 00:10:17,943
Those four keywords
should get the public's attention.

141
00:10:17,967 --> 00:10:21,076
We'll push that narrative in the media
and immediately file for annulment.

142
00:10:21,100 --> 00:10:22,276
These days,

143
00:10:22,300 --> 00:10:25,333
even the courts can't
ignore public opinion.

144
00:10:26,567 --> 00:10:28,509
Any record of Kim Yeong
Ran leaving the country?

145
00:10:28,533 --> 00:10:30,976
We checked, but no immigration records.

146
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:33,233
We're securing airport CCTV footage.

147
00:11:01,367 --> 00:11:02,776
Let me get that for you.

148
00:11:02,800 --> 00:11:04,833
No, I'm fine.

149
00:11:13,100 --> 00:11:14,967
Right this way, please.

150
00:11:18,333 --> 00:11:21,509
The principal urgently
requested living quarters,

151
00:11:21,533 --> 00:11:23,609
so we cleared out our storage shed.

152
00:11:23,633 --> 00:11:25,700
It's really far from
Seoul to Muchang, right?

153
00:11:27,233 --> 00:11:29,343
Yes.

154
00:11:29,367 --> 00:11:32,533
But, how did you hear about
and apply to Muchang Kindergarten?

155
00:11:34,033 --> 00:11:36,709
Muchang strawberries are famous, right?

156
00:11:36,733 --> 00:11:38,433
Are they?

157
00:11:39,200 --> 00:11:41,609
People eating them rarely check origins.

158
00:11:41,633 --> 00:11:44,309
I pay attention to those details.

159
00:11:44,333 --> 00:11:46,876
Honestly, you didn't come
for strawberries, right?

160
00:11:46,900 --> 00:11:49,200
Do you have relatives here?

161
00:11:51,933 --> 00:11:55,733
Must I answer every such question?

162
00:11:56,600 --> 00:11:59,633
No, no need.

163
00:12:03,067 --> 00:12:05,943
I heard you worked at Iseon Kindergarten.

164
00:12:05,967 --> 00:12:08,109
Can teachers be transferred mid-term?

165
00:12:08,133 --> 00:12:09,643
Yes, that's possible.

166
00:12:09,667 --> 00:12:12,776
Oh, I teach part-time PE
at Muchang Kindergarten too.

167
00:12:12,800 --> 00:12:14,700
My son attends there as well.

168
00:12:19,233 --> 00:12:21,409
Let me show you the shed.

169
00:12:21,433 --> 00:12:22,876
When you look at it,

170
00:12:22,900 --> 00:12:25,376
you'll see I personally
took care of every little detail.

171
00:12:25,400 --> 00:12:27,143
You built all this yourself?

172
00:12:27,167 --> 00:12:29,409
Well, pretty much built it myself.

173
00:12:29,433 --> 00:12:31,033
Come take a look.

174
00:12:31,933 --> 00:12:34,000
- Inside you'll see...
- Excuse me.

175
00:12:34,833 --> 00:12:36,833
I get the picture.

176
00:12:39,733 --> 00:12:41,743
But

177
00:12:41,767 --> 00:12:44,633
could you stop paying
so much attention to me?

178
00:12:55,200 --> 00:12:57,200
Totally rude.

179
00:13:03,267 --> 00:13:05,267
He can't possibly have
recognized me, right?

180
00:13:51,967 --> 00:13:53,576
Annoah.

181
00:13:53,600 --> 00:13:57,876
That teacher's pretty weird, right?

182
00:13:57,900 --> 00:14:00,300
Right? You think so too, huh?

183
00:14:01,233 --> 00:14:04,500
Let's keep a close eye on her, okay?

184
00:14:05,267 --> 00:14:07,843
What's with the vibe here today?

185
00:14:07,867 --> 00:14:10,667
Annoah, how is it? Can you see?

186
00:14:14,867 --> 00:14:16,109
Jeez.

187
00:14:16,133 --> 00:14:19,467
They say dogs see ghosts,
but maybe our Annoah can't see them.

188
00:14:25,267 --> 00:14:27,876
[Bites once: 'Annoah']
These days with the recession,

189
00:14:27,900 --> 00:14:31,109
a lot of people even get
spirit-invoking rituals on purpose.

190
00:14:31,133 --> 00:14:32,809
Aren't you doing it
because you don't want to go to work?

191
00:14:32,833 --> 00:14:35,467
Hey, I wanna do that too.

192
00:14:36,960 --> 00:14:39,096
Oh right.

193
00:14:40,967 --> 00:14:42,633
Where's the new teacher?

194
00:14:43,333 --> 00:14:45,000
There she is.

195
00:14:46,100 --> 00:14:47,700
What's she like?

196
00:14:48,467 --> 00:14:50,443
Rejects help when offered.

197
00:14:50,467 --> 00:14:51,776
Quite independent.

198
00:14:51,800 --> 00:14:53,576
She asked me if I'd ever seen her
somewhere before.

199
00:14:53,600 --> 00:14:55,909
Is she an influencer or something?

200
00:14:55,933 --> 00:14:57,076
Ah, no way.

201
00:14:57,100 --> 00:14:58,176
'No way'.

202
00:14:58,200 --> 00:15:01,743
Oh, right, didn't you
once deliver strawberries

203
00:15:01,767 --> 00:15:04,376
to the ramyeon chairman's place?

204
00:15:04,400 --> 00:15:05,409
I did.

205
00:15:05,433 --> 00:15:07,367
Hey, then check this article.

206
00:15:12,933 --> 00:15:14,776
[Female bodyguard 40 years younger marries
Late Chairman Ga Sung Ho, who is she really?]

207
00:15:14,800 --> 00:15:18,909
Then, do you know that bodyguard
who married the chairman?

208
00:15:18,933 --> 00:15:20,533
Have you seen her?

209
00:15:23,300 --> 00:15:25,200
Have I?

210
00:15:28,167 --> 00:15:30,876
[Chairman Ga Sung Ho's
Pistol Suicide, Hidden Truth]

211
00:15:30,900 --> 00:15:33,743
Check it out carefully.

212
00:15:33,767 --> 00:15:36,643
[Choking and punching!
[Kindergarten teacher's reckless violence]

213
00:15:36,667 --> 00:15:38,309
What is this?

214
00:15:38,333 --> 00:15:40,143
She's clearly a nasty woman, right?

215
00:15:40,167 --> 00:15:41,976
She's bad.

216
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:43,909
Nasty?

217
00:15:43,933 --> 00:15:47,476
People who hurt others like this
should be thrown in jail,

218
00:15:47,500 --> 00:15:49,643
cut off from society,
and don't even feed them prison meals.

219
00:15:49,667 --> 00:15:51,243
Don't even feed them prison meals.

220
00:15:51,267 --> 00:15:53,443
Seriously.

221
00:15:53,467 --> 00:15:55,709
I'm so pissed. I'll make pancakes.

222
00:15:55,733 --> 00:15:56,909
Pancakes, huh?

223
00:15:56,933 --> 00:16:00,033
I'm so angry. I'll drink makgeolli too.

224
00:16:14,167 --> 00:16:16,333
Did he recognize me or what?

225
00:16:58,333 --> 00:17:01,667
If people find out you married me,

226
00:17:02,733 --> 00:17:07,567
the whole world will point fingers
and condemn you mercilessly.

227
00:17:11,300 --> 00:17:16,167
Living a life like mine,
I've heard almost every insult out there.

228
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:28,467
The gun

229
00:17:29,133 --> 00:17:32,133
renders everything powerless.

230
00:17:33,067 --> 00:17:36,309
Even with your 3rd-degree taekwondo
and hapkido black belt,

231
00:17:36,333 --> 00:17:39,333
it means nothing against this.

232
00:17:50,600 --> 00:17:53,076
If a hitman comes,

233
00:17:53,100 --> 00:17:55,967
are you telling me to protect
myself with that gun?

234
00:17:56,700 --> 00:17:58,333
No.

235
00:18:00,067 --> 00:18:03,900
About Ye Rim's killer,

236
00:18:05,033 --> 00:18:09,000
my only way to punish them

237
00:18:10,867 --> 00:18:12,733
is through you.

238
00:18:30,533 --> 00:18:33,509
There's no guarantee
the same person will come, right?

239
00:18:33,533 --> 00:18:35,733
No guarantee,

240
00:18:36,800 --> 00:18:40,000
but there are people who don't change.

241
00:18:43,533 --> 00:18:46,733
Should I kill that person, Chairman?

242
00:18:48,033 --> 00:18:50,167
One of you two

243
00:18:50,900 --> 00:18:53,233
needs to survive.

244
00:18:55,533 --> 00:18:58,500
I want that survivor to be you.

245
00:19:09,433 --> 00:19:12,767
Murder carries at least
a five-year sentence.

246
00:19:13,467 --> 00:19:15,800
If I kill someone and serve five years.

247
00:19:16,867 --> 00:19:19,733
I don't want to stay longer than that.

248
00:19:21,133 --> 00:19:23,567
You can make that happen with money, right?

249
00:19:24,867 --> 00:19:27,667
What can't money fix?

250
00:19:29,700 --> 00:19:32,909
If I behave as a model
prisoner and get parole,

251
00:19:32,933 --> 00:19:35,843
I'd be in my mid-thirties when I get out.

252
00:19:35,867 --> 00:19:39,467
I want to start anew
somewhere unknown then.

253
00:19:40,367 --> 00:19:42,067
Okay.

254
00:19:43,400 --> 00:19:46,100
Even if you restart then,

255
00:19:46,900 --> 00:19:48,800
it won't be too late.

256
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:54,567
Five years is fair compensation.

257
00:20:01,467 --> 00:20:03,433
If I survive.

258
00:20:15,500 --> 00:20:17,567
I'm hungry.

259
00:20:43,767 --> 00:20:47,909
So I combed through
social media for our influencer.

260
00:20:47,933 --> 00:20:51,033
But I couldn't find the name 'Bu Se Mi'.

261
00:20:51,967 --> 00:20:55,333
It's just because she's
not a popular influencer.

262
00:20:58,167 --> 00:21:01,276
It's obvious now that
she's like a guy-version Tae Min.

263
00:21:01,300 --> 00:21:02,967
Darn it.

264
00:21:06,500 --> 00:21:07,843
It's too quiet.

265
00:21:07,867 --> 00:21:10,467
I wonder what she's doing.

266
00:21:12,500 --> 00:21:14,376
- Seo Tae Min.
- Yeah?

267
00:21:14,400 --> 00:21:16,976
I know you're being nice, but,

268
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:22,776
people reveal themselves
over time, you punk.

269
00:21:22,800 --> 00:21:27,700
So, you were dating for that long
and then boom, you had a kid?

270
00:21:29,733 --> 00:21:31,643
We were together long enough.

271
00:21:31,667 --> 00:21:33,776
But you know,

272
00:21:33,800 --> 00:21:36,109
you can't really know a person completely.

273
00:21:36,133 --> 00:21:39,076
Oh, spirit, you came for pancakes too?

274
00:21:39,100 --> 00:21:40,700
Ugh.

275
00:21:43,067 --> 00:21:45,667
Stop that. It's creepy.

276
00:21:52,533 --> 00:21:54,009
Pancakes. Pancakes.

277
00:21:54,033 --> 00:21:57,176
- You serve.
- Bring the pancake to her quickly.

278
00:21:57,200 --> 00:21:58,643
You go and tell her.

279
00:21:58,667 --> 00:22:00,300
Miss!

280
00:22:04,100 --> 00:22:06,143
You make pancakes?

281
00:22:06,167 --> 00:22:07,800
Huh?

282
00:22:09,067 --> 00:22:10,409
Can you cook pancakes?

283
00:22:10,433 --> 00:22:13,967
No, I'm not good at cooking them.

284
00:22:18,467 --> 00:22:21,343
You know I get tongue-tied around women.
Why would you make me talk to her?

285
00:22:21,367 --> 00:22:24,567
Where's she heading this evening?
I heard it's her first time in Muchang.

286
00:22:33,867 --> 00:22:37,043
We have an emergency meeting
regarding the new teacher.

287
00:22:37,067 --> 00:22:39,967
Come to Muchang Supermarket by 8 PM.

288
00:22:54,700 --> 00:22:58,109
Just keep an eye on that
person for three months,

289
00:22:58,133 --> 00:23:02,033
and we'll make them
permanent after three months.

290
00:23:03,800 --> 00:23:06,643
You said you're a lawyer, right?

291
00:23:06,667 --> 00:23:08,809
Yes, that's right.

292
00:23:08,833 --> 00:23:12,000
Looks like something good
happened to Yeong Ran?

293
00:23:13,267 --> 00:23:17,309
Actually, Kim Yeong Ran won the lottery.

294
00:23:17,333 --> 00:23:18,409
First prize.

295
00:23:18,433 --> 00:23:20,443
What? Oh my!

296
00:23:20,467 --> 00:23:22,733
- Keep it down.
- Oh.

297
00:23:23,633 --> 00:23:25,776
Sorry about that.

298
00:23:25,800 --> 00:23:28,709
That's amazing.

299
00:23:28,733 --> 00:23:31,009
So, my job is

300
00:23:31,033 --> 00:23:33,876
just to watch that person closely, right?

301
00:23:33,900 --> 00:23:35,767
Yes, exactly.

302
00:24:13,233 --> 00:24:14,833
You startled me.

303
00:24:23,300 --> 00:24:24,900
Come in, come in.

304
00:24:31,133 --> 00:24:36,333
[Private Investigation]

305
00:24:37,933 --> 00:24:39,309
Are you looking for her?

306
00:24:39,333 --> 00:24:41,376
Yes.

307
00:24:41,400 --> 00:24:43,476
What should we do if we find her?

308
00:24:43,500 --> 00:24:45,167
Kill her.

309
00:24:51,000 --> 00:24:53,376
How much money do you need?

310
00:24:53,400 --> 00:24:54,643
A single bill should do, right?

311
00:24:54,667 --> 00:24:56,333
Sir.

312
00:24:57,000 --> 00:24:59,876
Do you enjoy crime movies or dramas?

313
00:24:59,900 --> 00:25:02,333
What kind of nonsense
is this all of a sudden?

314
00:25:03,933 --> 00:25:07,109
You look perfectly normal.

315
00:25:07,133 --> 00:25:09,943
But you're so clueless
about how the world works.

316
00:25:09,967 --> 00:25:13,109
There's nowhere in Korea
without CCTV nowadays.

317
00:25:13,133 --> 00:25:17,109
If we kill someone, we'll
get caught immediately.

318
00:25:17,133 --> 00:25:18,833
This

319
00:25:21,700 --> 00:25:23,633
is our specialty.

320
00:25:25,933 --> 00:25:27,276
[We Handle Any Task]

321
00:25:27,300 --> 00:25:31,400
If you're not owed money
or missing someone, just leave.

322
00:25:32,867 --> 00:25:34,856
If you keep asking to kill someone

323
00:25:34,880 --> 00:25:37,867
over a measly 100 million won,

324
00:25:38,800 --> 00:25:41,167
I'll report you to the police.

325
00:25:43,533 --> 00:25:45,433
Report?

326
00:25:47,533 --> 00:25:50,643
Darn it, I made time to come here, hey.

327
00:25:50,667 --> 00:25:53,609
Then, who's gonna kill her, huh?

328
00:25:53,633 --> 00:25:55,776
Hold on.

329
00:25:55,800 --> 00:25:59,067
If you find her, you can hook us up
with someone to kill her, can't you?

330
00:26:00,200 --> 00:26:02,109
Well, sure.

331
00:26:02,133 --> 00:26:06,300
I do know people who
handle that sort of thing.

332
00:26:07,033 --> 00:26:08,933
But not us.

333
00:26:11,767 --> 00:26:14,433
First find her, then plan the next step.

334
00:26:15,733 --> 00:26:19,276
Please find this woman.

335
00:26:19,300 --> 00:26:21,000
Her mother too.

336
00:26:24,800 --> 00:26:27,633
Seems like someone you really want to find.

337
00:26:33,467 --> 00:26:35,333
I miss her

338
00:26:36,267 --> 00:26:38,467
so much that I could kill her.

339
00:26:40,533 --> 00:26:43,933
So if you want money, find her quickly.

340
00:26:45,500 --> 00:26:48,000
Looks like you're loaded.

341
00:27:03,100 --> 00:27:06,043
The strawberry farmhouse
is quite far from the village.

342
00:27:06,067 --> 00:27:08,576
There aren't many streetlights either.

343
00:27:08,600 --> 00:27:11,167
Someone could be killed there,
and no one would notice.

344
00:27:16,100 --> 00:27:18,309
Okay.

345
00:27:18,333 --> 00:27:21,043
[Muchang Supermarket, Lottery 1st
Prize Winner] Now, just say it straight.

346
00:27:21,067 --> 00:27:24,409
Our Ju Won started kindergarten at five
and by the time he turned seven,

347
00:27:24,433 --> 00:27:27,409
five different teachers
had come and gone, right?

348
00:27:27,433 --> 00:27:29,176
- Yes.
- Correct.

349
00:27:29,200 --> 00:27:33,043
But they all vanished
without saying goodbye, right?

350
00:27:33,067 --> 00:27:34,876
- Exactly.
- That's right.

351
00:27:34,900 --> 00:27:36,709
Three of them

352
00:27:36,733 --> 00:27:39,933
stole supplies, embezzled snack funds,

353
00:27:42,467 --> 00:27:43,476
and had affairs.

354
00:27:43,500 --> 00:27:46,909
- Never pegged them for that.
- Shocking.

355
00:27:46,933 --> 00:27:49,176
The other two made promises.

356
00:27:49,200 --> 00:27:53,500
They told the kids,
'I'll stay till graduation, promise.'

357
00:27:55,000 --> 00:27:56,600
3 million won.

358
00:27:58,167 --> 00:27:59,309
Thank you.

359
00:27:59,333 --> 00:28:01,109
They took the money Seong Tae handed them,

360
00:28:01,133 --> 00:28:03,443
couldn't even last three months,
then quit and ran off.

361
00:28:03,467 --> 00:28:05,376
- Right.
- Exactly.

362
00:28:05,400 --> 00:28:07,676
So, the kids cried and were a mess, right?

363
00:28:07,700 --> 00:28:09,576
- Absolutely.
- Yeah.

364
00:28:09,600 --> 00:28:12,943
I hate seeing the kids get hurt.

365
00:28:12,967 --> 00:28:15,143
Me too.

366
00:28:15,167 --> 00:28:17,643
Dong Min, I get how you feel.

367
00:28:17,667 --> 00:28:20,143
But without a teacher,
the kindergarten would have to close.

368
00:28:20,167 --> 00:28:22,809
Yeah, maybe this time will be different.

369
00:28:22,833 --> 00:28:25,509
Still, throwing a welcome
party might be too much.

370
00:28:25,533 --> 00:28:28,643
But we can't just do
nothing for a newcomer...

371
00:28:28,667 --> 00:28:31,443
Did you see the news today?

372
00:28:31,467 --> 00:28:35,309
A kindergarten teacher hitting kids
was the headline.

373
00:28:35,333 --> 00:28:36,712
Really?

374
00:28:36,736 --> 00:28:39,376
- What?
- How could it be?

375
00:28:39,400 --> 00:28:42,133
Never judge a book by its cover.

376
00:28:49,567 --> 00:28:51,867
Raising kids is no joke.

377
00:28:56,100 --> 00:28:57,900
Haven't seen her before.

378
00:29:00,233 --> 00:29:02,109
It's her! It's the teacher!

379
00:29:02,133 --> 00:29:04,209
- The teacher's here!
- Get her a drink!

380
00:29:04,233 --> 00:29:06,216
We should've prepared something!

381
00:29:06,240 --> 00:29:08,809
Oh my, what now?

382
00:29:08,833 --> 00:29:10,967
Oh, no.

383
00:29:12,800 --> 00:29:14,676
Welcome.

384
00:29:14,700 --> 00:29:16,467
Welcome.

385
00:29:23,267 --> 00:29:25,343
Where's the ramyeon?

386
00:29:25,367 --> 00:29:27,633
Over there.

387
00:30:01,333 --> 00:30:04,243
Miss, you haven't eaten dinner, have you?

388
00:30:04,267 --> 00:30:06,433
There's nothing to eat at home.

389
00:30:12,533 --> 00:30:15,267
Meals are included in the rent.

390
00:30:20,067 --> 00:30:22,243
Why mention that now?

391
00:30:22,267 --> 00:30:24,633
Earlier, you told me to shut up.

392
00:30:25,533 --> 00:30:28,100
It's late tonight. I'll have ramyeon.

393
00:30:30,867 --> 00:30:34,000
Wait, you're not giving her food?

394
00:30:35,000 --> 00:30:36,376
Should I... carry it?

395
00:30:36,400 --> 00:30:39,443
- Pardon?
- Should I bring it in for you?

396
00:30:39,467 --> 00:30:43,033
No, it's fine. I'll take it.

397
00:30:44,567 --> 00:30:45,709
Take care.

398
00:30:45,733 --> 00:30:47,676
Goodbye.

399
00:30:47,700 --> 00:30:49,333
Go ahead.

400
00:30:53,467 --> 00:30:56,109
[Muchang Supermarket,
881st Lottery 1st Prize Winner]

401
00:30:56,133 --> 00:30:58,309
- She left.
- Hey, you...

402
00:30:58,333 --> 00:30:59,343
You're just...

403
00:30:59,367 --> 00:31:00,376
Did you all see that?

404
00:31:00,400 --> 00:31:01,843
She doesn't seem
like a kindergarten teacher at all.

405
00:31:01,867 --> 00:31:03,676
We need to watch her closely. Seriously.

406
00:31:03,700 --> 00:31:05,209
Look, aside from just watching,

407
00:31:05,233 --> 00:31:07,143
you need to feed her, right?

408
00:31:07,167 --> 00:31:08,709
You go with her too, Dong Min.

409
00:31:08,733 --> 00:31:09,876
- Go now!
- No...

410
00:31:09,900 --> 00:31:12,343
- Go quickly.
- Wait a second.

411
00:31:12,344 --> 00:31:32,640
Officail Website : dramacool.club

412
00:31:32,664 --> 00:31:52,344
Translate by =Qari= @Team Viki

413
00:31:12,367 --> 00:31:13,676
Go now.

414
00:31:13,700 --> 00:31:15,643
No, I said let's talk.

415
00:31:15,667 --> 00:31:16,676
You need to feed her, alright?

416
00:31:16,700 --> 00:31:18,543
- Go feed her now.
- Go quickly.

417
00:31:18,567 --> 00:31:20,267
Follow her back.

418
00:31:21,467 --> 00:31:23,800
- Go.
- After her.

419
00:31:26,967 --> 00:31:28,900
Let's go in.

420
00:31:43,300 --> 00:31:46,676
Miss, I'm heading home too.

421
00:31:46,700 --> 00:31:48,467
Don't be suspicious.

422
00:31:58,967 --> 00:32:00,600
That extra

423
00:32:02,033 --> 00:32:03,833
sure talks a lot.

424
00:32:04,533 --> 00:32:07,109
If we can't find a teacher this time either,

425
00:32:07,133 --> 00:32:09,776
Muchang Kindergarten itself
will shut down next year.

426
00:32:09,800 --> 00:32:13,509
Then, our kids will have to ride the
shuttle bus for over an hour to get out.

427
00:32:13,533 --> 00:32:15,376
Our jobs will disappear too.

428
00:32:15,400 --> 00:32:17,376
Exactly.

429
00:32:17,400 --> 00:32:20,109
Plus, she's a teacher
from Iseon Women's University.

430
00:32:20,133 --> 00:32:24,843
It's a golden chance for our kids to get
Seoul-level quality education.

431
00:32:24,867 --> 00:32:26,709
- Right, a golden chance.
- Exactly.

432
00:32:26,733 --> 00:32:28,309
We're all on the same page, right?

433
00:32:28,333 --> 00:32:29,443
- Obviously.
- Of course.

434
00:32:29,467 --> 00:32:31,376
Until our kids graduate,

435
00:32:31,400 --> 00:32:33,109
we have to somehow keep that teacher

436
00:32:33,133 --> 00:32:36,043
at Iseon Muchang Kindergarten.

437
00:32:36,067 --> 00:32:37,776
- Keep her!
- Yes.

438
00:32:37,800 --> 00:32:39,409
But how do we keep her?

439
00:32:39,433 --> 00:32:44,100
If Seong Tae uses cash bribes,
we honestly have no alternatives.

440
00:32:45,533 --> 00:32:48,443
What if we do something for her?

441
00:32:48,467 --> 00:32:50,367
Like cooking meals.

442
00:32:51,300 --> 00:32:55,009
Speaking from my
experience living in Seoul,

443
00:32:55,033 --> 00:32:58,876
Seoul people tend to be wary
if someone is overly kind for no reason.

444
00:32:58,900 --> 00:33:01,176
First, you have to subtly take care of her,

445
00:33:01,200 --> 00:33:03,576
pretending not to notice.

446
00:33:03,600 --> 00:33:06,109
Absolutely without her knowing.
Never make her feel burdened.

447
00:33:06,133 --> 00:33:07,343
Just casually.

448
00:33:07,367 --> 00:33:11,109
Wait, why didn't Dongwaru come?

449
00:33:11,133 --> 00:33:13,543
- Dongwaru?
- He never misses these meetings.

450
00:33:13,567 --> 00:33:15,476
- Busy?
- Strange.

451
00:33:15,500 --> 00:33:16,576
[Ex-chef at Seoul Shinsung Hotel, Dongwaru]

452
00:33:16,600 --> 00:33:20,676
It's past 8:30. Do we still
need to go to the supermarket?

453
00:33:20,700 --> 00:33:25,043
I heard this teacher
came from Iseon Kindergarten in Seoul.

454
00:33:25,067 --> 00:33:27,676
Lives in Gangnam, rich parents.

455
00:33:27,700 --> 00:33:30,509
No idea why someone so loaded
would come down here.

456
00:33:30,533 --> 00:33:34,009
Seriously, we're not
going to get caught, right?

457
00:33:34,033 --> 00:33:36,276
My heart's pounding.

458
00:33:36,300 --> 00:33:38,367
Should we change the sign?

459
00:33:39,533 --> 00:33:43,776
I spent three months just peeling onions
in the Shinsung Hotel kitchen.

460
00:33:43,800 --> 00:33:45,809
She's supposedly a rich girl.

461
00:33:45,833 --> 00:33:48,809
She must've been to Shinsung Hotel.

462
00:33:48,833 --> 00:33:50,809
One taste, and she'd recognize it.

463
00:33:50,833 --> 00:33:53,809
Se A, our youngest, is in her class, right?

464
00:33:53,833 --> 00:33:56,400
We can't avoid her. What do we do?

465
00:33:58,300 --> 00:34:01,109
Honey, don't worry.

466
00:34:01,133 --> 00:34:03,343
Last time, other teachers

467
00:34:03,367 --> 00:34:05,643
all ran away within three months.

468
00:34:05,667 --> 00:34:06,676
True.

469
00:34:06,700 --> 00:34:08,443
Let's endure a bit longer.

470
00:34:08,467 --> 00:34:12,376
That woman won't last in Muchang either.

471
00:34:12,400 --> 00:34:13,909
Until then, Ms. Bu Su Mi

472
00:34:13,933 --> 00:34:16,276
isn't allowed in our Dongwaru!

473
00:34:16,300 --> 00:34:17,343
Not allowed!

474
00:34:17,367 --> 00:34:19,309
Okay.

475
00:34:19,333 --> 00:34:20,967
Clever.

476
00:34:29,233 --> 00:34:31,376
Let me.

477
00:34:31,400 --> 00:34:33,233
What are you doing right now?

478
00:34:33,900 --> 00:34:36,967
I'm just apologizing
for not taking care of your meals.

479
00:34:38,267 --> 00:34:39,776
Is that really all?

480
00:34:39,800 --> 00:34:42,533
Then, should there be anything more?

481
00:34:43,300 --> 00:34:45,643
Do you always reject kindness like this?

482
00:34:45,667 --> 00:34:48,576
Kindness is only kind
if the receiver feels it as such.

483
00:34:48,600 --> 00:34:50,343
Jeez.

484
00:34:50,367 --> 00:34:53,576
From now on, breakfast will be
at 8 and dinner at 7.

485
00:34:53,600 --> 00:34:55,609
If you have time, come and eat together.

486
00:34:55,633 --> 00:34:57,109
I'll handle that myself.

487
00:34:57,133 --> 00:34:59,576
This isn't kindness.
It's what your money paid for.

488
00:34:59,600 --> 00:35:01,967
You don't have any
food restrictions, right?

489
00:35:05,933 --> 00:35:08,176
Rice mixed with beans.

490
00:35:08,200 --> 00:35:09,443
Bean rice.

491
00:35:09,467 --> 00:35:11,109
Wow, seriously.

492
00:35:11,133 --> 00:35:12,476
Seriously what?

493
00:35:12,500 --> 00:35:15,267
First adult I've seen
who can't eat bean rice.

494
00:35:21,500 --> 00:35:23,109
Ugh.

495
00:35:23,133 --> 00:35:25,000
Don't even ask.

496
00:35:28,733 --> 00:35:31,376
[Muchang gold medalist drops out of national
team] He will be your landlord, Madam.

497
00:35:31,400 --> 00:35:34,143
He's actually my cousin,

498
00:35:34,167 --> 00:35:36,843
but honestly stay away from him.

499
00:35:36,867 --> 00:35:38,976
It's better for you.

500
00:35:39,000 --> 00:35:40,443
Why?

501
00:35:40,467 --> 00:35:42,643
You know the 'crazy dog, ' right?

502
00:35:42,667 --> 00:35:45,209
When Jeon Dong Min snaps,

503
00:35:45,233 --> 00:35:47,600
no one in Muchang dares cross him.

504
00:35:51,367 --> 00:35:53,767
I don't think he's that crazy, though.

505
00:36:56,300 --> 00:36:58,300
- Shh.
- Shh.

506
00:37:04,000 --> 00:37:05,409
Teacher?

507
00:37:05,433 --> 00:37:07,576
Teacher?

508
00:37:07,600 --> 00:37:09,109
Oh, yeah, yeah.

509
00:37:09,133 --> 00:37:10,409
I'm Ms. Bu Se Mi.

510
00:37:10,433 --> 00:37:11,410
But who are you?

511
00:37:11,434 --> 00:37:15,843
Dad told me not to give
my heart easily to the new teacher.

512
00:37:15,867 --> 00:37:17,076
What's that supposed to mean?

513
00:37:17,100 --> 00:37:18,143
I don't know either.

514
00:37:18,167 --> 00:37:19,767
Jeon Ju Won!

515
00:37:20,800 --> 00:37:23,043
Ms. Bu Se Mi!

516
00:37:23,067 --> 00:37:25,867
Sorry, I'll just come in for a moment.

517
00:37:38,367 --> 00:37:40,633
Jeon Ju Won hiding inside the tent.

518
00:37:42,067 --> 00:37:45,067
And why are you hiding there, Miss?

519
00:37:54,967 --> 00:37:56,600
Jeon Ju Won.

520
00:37:57,533 --> 00:38:00,843
Who told you to sneak
into the teacher's cabin?

521
00:38:00,867 --> 00:38:03,176
This used to be my hideout.

522
00:38:03,200 --> 00:38:06,343
But now it's where I live.

523
00:38:06,367 --> 00:38:09,409
This was his hideout when it was empty.

524
00:38:09,433 --> 00:38:10,643
He won't do it again.

525
00:38:10,667 --> 00:38:16,400
Dad, I heard her stomach growl
about three times earlier.

526
00:38:19,267 --> 00:38:21,800
It was just once, not three times.

527
00:38:22,533 --> 00:38:24,009
Let's go.

528
00:38:24,033 --> 00:38:27,867
If you come here again, you'll get scolded.

529
00:38:29,533 --> 00:38:32,009
Make sure to have dinner.

530
00:38:32,033 --> 00:38:33,176
Uh, I...

531
00:38:33,200 --> 00:38:34,909
Yes.

532
00:38:34,933 --> 00:38:37,009
Well

533
00:38:37,033 --> 00:38:41,109
I just... couldn't buy the kimchi.

534
00:38:41,133 --> 00:38:43,843
Could I ask for some kimchi?

535
00:38:43,867 --> 00:38:46,643
Miss, I'll bring you some.

536
00:38:46,667 --> 00:38:48,900
Hey, if you put on your shoes there.

537
00:38:54,333 --> 00:38:56,200
I'll bring it to you.

538
00:38:57,200 --> 00:38:58,967
Jeon Ju Won, come with me.

539
00:39:15,300 --> 00:39:20,400
Dad told me not to give
my heart easily to the new teacher.

540
00:39:25,633 --> 00:39:27,667
I don't plan to give it either.

541
00:39:38,367 --> 00:39:43,167
[CCTV installation]

542
00:39:44,167 --> 00:39:46,267
[CCTV installation]

543
00:39:47,667 --> 00:39:49,409
- Now, leave.
- Wait a second.

544
00:39:49,433 --> 00:39:50,676
- Wait, just...
- Why?

545
00:39:50,700 --> 00:39:52,543
Open it up.

546
00:39:52,567 --> 00:39:54,643
This is trespassing.

547
00:39:54,667 --> 00:39:58,176
Attorney Lee, why should we leave?

548
00:39:58,200 --> 00:39:59,848
- Hey.
- What?

549
00:39:59,872 --> 00:40:02,776
Uh, this... It's that.

550
00:40:02,800 --> 00:40:04,076
This is wrongful termination.

551
00:40:04,100 --> 00:40:05,109
Yes, wrongful termination.

552
00:40:05,133 --> 00:40:06,343
Wrongful termination?

553
00:40:06,367 --> 00:40:07,609
Isn't it?

554
00:40:07,633 --> 00:40:09,143
Wrongful termination.

555
00:40:09,167 --> 00:40:10,743
A deal?

556
00:40:10,767 --> 00:40:15,209
Wrongful termination means an employer
can't fire someone without just cause.

557
00:40:15,233 --> 00:40:18,076
The key here is 'just cause.'

558
00:40:18,100 --> 00:40:20,576
Let's set aside legal
terms and speak plainly.

559
00:40:20,600 --> 00:40:22,976
Butler Choi and Mr. Yang Cheol Su.

560
00:40:23,000 --> 00:40:24,643
- Yes.
- Right here.

561
00:40:24,667 --> 00:40:26,809
Who are your employers?

562
00:40:26,833 --> 00:40:29,776
Cheol Su! Chairman Ga Sung Ho!

563
00:40:29,800 --> 00:40:31,909
- Wrong!
- Kim Yeong Ran! Madam!

564
00:40:31,933 --> 00:40:33,009
Correct answer.

565
00:40:33,033 --> 00:40:35,076
- I was about to say that...
- Hey.

566
00:40:35,100 --> 00:40:37,109
This isn't the time to celebrate.

567
00:40:37,133 --> 00:40:38,709
After Chairman Ga Sung Ho passed away,

568
00:40:38,733 --> 00:40:41,109
Ms. Kim Yeong Ran
naturally became the owner.

569
00:40:41,133 --> 00:40:44,109
Meaning your employer is Ms. Kim Yeong Ran.

570
00:40:44,133 --> 00:40:45,176
But you two,

571
00:40:45,200 --> 00:40:47,409
do you both realize
what you've done to your employer?

572
00:40:47,433 --> 00:40:49,843
No, that's...

573
00:40:49,867 --> 00:40:52,976
Since the previous owner
suddenly passed away,

574
00:40:53,000 --> 00:40:54,909
- the handover...
- The handover

575
00:40:54,933 --> 00:40:57,676
wasn't properly done, so we made a mistake.

576
00:40:57,700 --> 00:40:59,843
'A dog that's bitten
once tends to bite again.'

577
00:40:59,867 --> 00:41:02,409
Attorney Lee, calling me
a dog? That's Cheol Su.

578
00:41:02,433 --> 00:41:03,409
Oh, are you talking to me?

579
00:41:03,433 --> 00:41:04,410
You called me a dog?

580
00:41:04,434 --> 00:41:07,343
Attorney Lee, I won't bite again.

581
00:41:07,367 --> 00:41:10,276
Wait, I'll pull out my fangs.

582
00:41:10,300 --> 00:41:11,843
I've added some severance pay.

583
00:41:11,867 --> 00:41:14,167
- Take this at least.
- Thank you.

584
00:41:15,233 --> 00:41:16,833
Wait.

585
00:41:18,233 --> 00:41:19,643
Butler.

586
00:41:19,667 --> 00:41:21,376
Yang Cheol Su.

587
00:41:21,400 --> 00:41:24,309
Listen carefully from now on.

588
00:41:24,333 --> 00:41:27,809
I listened to you and ended up like this.

589
00:41:27,833 --> 00:41:29,109
Ah, our Hye Ji.

590
00:41:29,133 --> 00:41:31,567
Hye Ji said she has 100 million in savings.

591
00:41:32,467 --> 00:41:35,743
I know who we should turn to.

592
00:41:35,767 --> 00:41:37,476
Who is that?

593
00:41:37,500 --> 00:41:39,109
Who else?

594
00:41:39,133 --> 00:41:40,509
The professor.

595
00:41:40,533 --> 00:41:43,733
She must have a plan.

596
00:41:47,367 --> 00:41:49,752
Wait, wait. Wait for me.

597
00:42:28,900 --> 00:42:31,133
Only my back hurts.

598
00:42:45,800 --> 00:42:47,743
Wow, chicken.

599
00:42:47,767 --> 00:42:50,309
I'll stay here until Madam returns.

600
00:42:50,333 --> 00:42:52,676
Act like you're invisible, Ms. Baek Hye Ji.

601
00:42:52,700 --> 00:42:54,676
Attorney Lee, have you eaten?

602
00:42:54,700 --> 00:42:56,043
Didn't I tell you?

603
00:42:56,067 --> 00:42:59,643
'Leave the cooking to the chef,
and the chicken to the chicken shop.'

604
00:42:59,667 --> 00:43:02,343
Don't want homemade food?

605
00:43:02,367 --> 00:43:04,143
This isn't my home.

606
00:43:04,167 --> 00:43:05,409
Ah, one more thing,

607
00:43:05,433 --> 00:43:09,276
stay out of the main house
except during meals, Ms. Baek Hye Ji.

608
00:43:09,300 --> 00:43:10,409
Alright.

609
00:43:10,433 --> 00:43:13,200
Attorney, you know, um...

610
00:43:15,300 --> 00:43:19,267
Where exactly is Madam?

611
00:43:20,800 --> 00:43:24,033
Why should I have to explain that
to you, Ms. Baek Hye Ji?

612
00:43:25,500 --> 00:43:28,276
Because Madam and I are friends.
You little troublemaker.

613
00:43:28,300 --> 00:43:31,033
Have you heard from
Professor Ga Seon Yeong?

614
00:43:31,833 --> 00:43:32,843
No.

615
00:43:32,867 --> 00:43:37,867
If Professor Ga approaches you even once,
tell me immediately, Ms. Baek Hye Ji.

616
00:43:38,633 --> 00:43:40,267
Okay.

617
00:43:41,333 --> 00:43:45,209
Yes... Why do I have to tell you?

618
00:43:45,233 --> 00:43:48,309
Listen to people until the end.

619
00:43:48,333 --> 00:43:49,933
Hmph.

620
00:44:10,200 --> 00:44:12,500
Muchang must be peaceful, right?

621
00:44:51,333 --> 00:44:53,376
Dong Min, did you talk
with the teacher yesterday?

622
00:44:53,400 --> 00:44:57,176
Does she prefer spicy red ramyeon? Or mild?

623
00:44:57,200 --> 00:44:58,833
Don't know.

624
00:45:00,233 --> 00:45:03,076
Do you think she likes soju? Or beer?

625
00:45:03,100 --> 00:45:05,709
Wait, she probably prefers wine. Right?

626
00:45:05,733 --> 00:45:07,109
No idea.

627
00:45:07,133 --> 00:45:09,443
Ugh, you two barely talked.

628
00:45:09,467 --> 00:45:11,209
No progress at all.

629
00:45:11,233 --> 00:45:13,209
She hates bean rice. Bean rice!

630
00:45:13,233 --> 00:45:16,143
Whoa, how'd you figure
that out? Impressive.

631
00:45:16,167 --> 00:45:18,276
Did things already move forward?

632
00:45:18,300 --> 00:45:21,667
Jeez. What could a single
guy like you even know?

633
00:45:23,833 --> 00:45:26,309
We even changed the strawberry variety
using the agricultural loan.

634
00:45:26,333 --> 00:45:29,076
Why are the seedlings so wilted?

635
00:45:29,100 --> 00:45:30,309
Hey, guys.

636
00:45:30,333 --> 00:45:31,743
You need to grow big and strong.

637
00:45:31,767 --> 00:45:35,076
So Ju Won can go to cram school
and learn piano. Right?

638
00:45:35,100 --> 00:45:36,733
Don't you agree?

639
00:45:37,933 --> 00:45:41,333
Don't worry, Uncle Dong
Min. We'll strike it rich.

640
00:45:42,100 --> 00:45:43,867
Another new spirit.

641
00:45:46,033 --> 00:45:48,867
Hey, I'll go wake Ju Won, okay?

642
00:45:49,767 --> 00:45:51,800
Seriously.

643
00:45:52,733 --> 00:45:54,776
But,

644
00:45:54,800 --> 00:45:58,500
strawberries won't make us rich.

645
00:46:04,767 --> 00:46:06,933
They're sweet! Sweet.

646
00:46:07,600 --> 00:46:09,967
Uncle Dong Min's an idiot.

647
00:46:12,567 --> 00:46:14,433
When did you get here?

648
00:46:29,900 --> 00:46:30,943
Oh, hi.

649
00:46:30,967 --> 00:46:32,343
- Hello, Ju Won.
- There you go.

650
00:46:32,367 --> 00:46:34,143
- Hello.
- Hello.

651
00:46:34,167 --> 00:46:36,276
- Hello.
- Hello.

652
00:46:36,300 --> 00:46:38,443
Jeon Ju Won, listen to your teacher.

653
00:46:38,467 --> 00:46:40,443
- Okay.
- We're late.

654
00:46:40,467 --> 00:46:42,067
See you.

655
00:46:49,100 --> 00:46:50,809
Ms. Bu Se Mi.

656
00:46:50,833 --> 00:46:53,709
This is Lee Mi Seon,
Principal of Iseon Kindergarten.

657
00:46:53,733 --> 00:46:58,009
I've been preoccupied
with the academic conference.

658
00:46:58,033 --> 00:47:00,843
Due to kindergarten circumstances,
we need you to start teaching immediately.

659
00:47:00,867 --> 00:47:04,509
Please arrive by 8:30 AM.

660
00:47:04,533 --> 00:47:05,843
Dong Min. Dong Min.

661
00:47:05,867 --> 00:47:08,443
- Yes?
- How is she?

662
00:47:08,467 --> 00:47:10,976
Don sent her all the
way to the kindergarten.

663
00:47:11,000 --> 00:47:13,676
I feel like he's subtly
trying to introduce her to me.

664
00:47:13,700 --> 00:47:14,909
Introduce her?

665
00:47:14,933 --> 00:47:17,743
He wants me to vet her
as his potential match.

666
00:47:17,767 --> 00:47:20,967
Top education, good family background.
Perfect for Don, right?

667
00:47:21,600 --> 00:47:24,243
Then do a thorough background check, sis.

668
00:47:24,267 --> 00:47:26,943
People fake degrees and
careers these days, right?

669
00:47:26,967 --> 00:47:31,343
Check her past
workplaces for any incidents.

670
00:47:31,367 --> 00:47:32,443
Dong Min.

671
00:47:32,467 --> 00:47:33,643
You don't know who I am?

672
00:47:33,667 --> 00:47:34,843
Lee Mi Seon.

673
00:47:34,867 --> 00:47:36,667
Already verified everything.

674
00:47:39,933 --> 00:47:41,733
I'm heading to work first.

675
00:47:54,400 --> 00:47:55,876
Hello, children.

676
00:47:55,900 --> 00:47:58,709
I'm Ms. Bu Se Mi.

677
00:47:58,733 --> 00:48:00,776
Hello, children.

678
00:48:00,800 --> 00:48:03,709
I'm Ms. Bu Se Mi.

679
00:48:03,733 --> 00:48:05,367
Okay.

680
00:48:09,900 --> 00:48:11,609
Yes.

681
00:48:11,633 --> 00:48:14,009
I'd like to inquire about installing CCTV.

682
00:48:14,033 --> 00:48:15,843
Can it be done today?

683
00:48:15,867 --> 00:48:17,700
Money isn't an issue.

684
00:48:29,167 --> 00:48:31,476
Hey, is this Kim Yeong Ran?

685
00:48:31,500 --> 00:48:32,843
Yes, correct.

686
00:48:32,867 --> 00:48:35,943
We verified multiple times
through airport CCTV footage.

687
00:48:35,967 --> 00:48:37,309
Then, where is she now?

688
00:48:37,333 --> 00:48:38,376
We're tracking her.

689
00:48:38,400 --> 00:48:41,176
Seoul's CCTV isn't accessible to everyone.

690
00:48:41,200 --> 00:48:43,333
It's challenging to trace her.

691
00:48:44,100 --> 00:48:47,143
Wow, unbelievable.

692
00:48:47,167 --> 00:48:49,076
What is she doing in the meantime?

693
00:48:49,100 --> 00:48:52,776
Professor, Lee Don changed the will's
release date to the shareholders' meeting.

694
00:48:52,800 --> 00:48:55,343
All heirs must attend.

695
00:48:55,367 --> 00:48:57,976
We need to obtain it before then.

696
00:48:58,000 --> 00:49:00,509
I already checked all bank VIP vaults.

697
00:49:00,533 --> 00:49:04,476
No traces under the chairman's name,
Lee Don's, or anyone else's.

698
00:49:04,500 --> 00:49:07,143
Ga Sung Ho trusts no one.

699
00:49:07,167 --> 00:49:09,033
He probably kept it at home.

700
00:49:10,067 --> 00:49:11,743
Contact Prosecutor Kim.

701
00:49:11,767 --> 00:49:14,209
Pin any charge on Lee Don
to drag him out of his house.

702
00:49:14,233 --> 00:49:15,867
Yes, Professor.

703
00:49:20,600 --> 00:49:24,276
I love these photos. Send me the best ones.

704
00:49:24,300 --> 00:49:26,743
We should file a missing person report.

705
00:49:26,767 --> 00:49:29,200
Mom left home.

706
00:49:31,100 --> 00:49:33,700
Should her children just stay silent?

707
00:49:44,333 --> 00:49:47,200
[Enrollment open year-round
at Muchang Iseon Kindergarten]

708
00:49:48,900 --> 00:49:51,533
[Security CCTV in operation]

709
00:50:01,533 --> 00:50:06,833
[Iseon Kindergarten]

710
00:50:09,667 --> 00:50:12,633
[Resume]

711
00:50:13,733 --> 00:50:17,109
You've done a lot of volunteer work abroad?

712
00:50:17,133 --> 00:50:20,076
Both my parents were active volunteers.

713
00:50:20,100 --> 00:50:22,376
I think I inherited that from them.

714
00:50:22,400 --> 00:50:26,743
Exactly. Family background matters.

715
00:50:26,767 --> 00:50:28,709
But with credentials
like yours, Ms. Bu Se Mi,

716
00:50:28,733 --> 00:50:32,309
you could've easily gotten into Iseon
Women's University Affiliated Kindergarten.

717
00:50:32,333 --> 00:50:34,176
Ah...

718
00:50:34,200 --> 00:50:38,200
Why did you come all the way to Muchang?

719
00:50:39,933 --> 00:50:42,143
I'm about to

720
00:50:42,167 --> 00:50:44,667
tell you the reason now.

721
00:50:49,333 --> 00:50:52,343
Since childhood, I
followed my professor father

722
00:50:52,367 --> 00:50:54,409
living abroad at times.

723
00:50:54,433 --> 00:50:57,809
During college breaks,
I volunteered in Africa

724
00:50:57,833 --> 00:51:02,143
and realized education's
crucial importance.

725
00:51:02,167 --> 00:51:03,609
Then I heard about

726
00:51:03,633 --> 00:51:08,843
a principal in Muchang
embodying Iseon's spirit.

727
00:51:08,867 --> 00:51:12,967
I desperately wanted
to teach children here.

728
00:51:14,167 --> 00:51:18,109
You're exactly the teacher
we've been waiting for.

729
00:51:18,133 --> 00:51:20,809
And arriving just before orientation,

730
00:51:20,833 --> 00:51:24,633
we're so fortunate to have
someone like you, Ms. Bu Se Mi.

731
00:51:26,667 --> 00:51:30,109
Shall we see the classrooms now?

732
00:51:30,133 --> 00:51:32,343
The children will arrive by shuttle soon.

733
00:51:32,367 --> 00:51:33,909
You can leave your bag here.

734
00:51:33,933 --> 00:51:37,200
Muchang is a safe place.

735
00:51:38,900 --> 00:51:40,600
This way.

736
00:51:41,633 --> 00:51:43,743
Our Muchang Iseon Kindergarten

737
00:51:43,767 --> 00:51:45,843
is the most prestigious in the area.

738
00:51:45,867 --> 00:51:49,167
Many children commute from far away.

739
00:51:52,600 --> 00:51:54,967
Aren't they adorable?

740
00:51:55,867 --> 00:51:58,243
Principal! Where are you?

741
00:51:58,267 --> 00:51:59,676
Come out and talk to me.

742
00:51:59,700 --> 00:52:03,609
Oh my, what's going on this morning?

743
00:52:03,633 --> 00:52:05,876
Miss, the Strawberry
Class is at the far end.

744
00:52:05,900 --> 00:52:07,800
Please go ahead first.

745
00:52:08,633 --> 00:52:10,243
What's this?

746
00:52:10,267 --> 00:52:12,309
How many times have I said
I won't renew the contract next year...

747
00:52:12,333 --> 00:52:13,343
Please calm down.

748
00:52:13,367 --> 00:52:15,509
Wait in the Apple Class.

749
00:52:15,533 --> 00:52:17,809
Go inside. To the Apple Class.

750
00:52:17,833 --> 00:52:19,309
Go in.

751
00:52:19,333 --> 00:52:21,167
Go in.

752
00:52:25,867 --> 00:52:28,276
The owner of this land
is nearing the end of his life.

753
00:52:28,300 --> 00:52:31,109
And his kids promised to sell me this land.

754
00:52:31,133 --> 00:52:32,843
I'll pay the full deposit tomorrow.

755
00:52:32,867 --> 00:52:36,909
I'm going to bulldoze this
garden and playground

756
00:52:36,933 --> 00:52:38,009
and build a nursing home.

757
00:52:38,033 --> 00:52:40,209
Seong Tae.

758
00:52:40,233 --> 00:52:41,676
Did you tear this?

759
00:52:41,700 --> 00:52:43,333
Yes.

760
00:52:44,033 --> 00:52:45,676
Seong Tae.

761
00:52:45,700 --> 00:52:47,443
If this kindergarten closes,

762
00:52:47,467 --> 00:52:51,409
kids will spend hours commuting by bus.

763
00:52:51,433 --> 00:52:55,043
But Principal, you know what?

764
00:52:55,067 --> 00:52:58,876
Soon there'll be more
elders needing nursing homes

765
00:52:58,900 --> 00:53:01,667
than kids attending this kindergarten.

766
00:53:02,467 --> 00:53:04,643
That's just reality.

767
00:53:04,667 --> 00:53:06,043
Market demand

768
00:53:06,067 --> 00:53:08,576
changes with the times.

769
00:53:08,600 --> 00:53:10,609
Understand?

770
00:53:10,633 --> 00:53:12,567
What demand? You...

771
00:53:13,733 --> 00:53:15,709
Take this.

772
00:53:15,733 --> 00:53:17,776
Take it, you bedwetter.

773
00:53:17,800 --> 00:53:19,400
What?

774
00:53:21,500 --> 00:53:23,843
[Ddu]

775
00:53:23,867 --> 00:53:24,943
Kang Seong Tae.

776
00:53:24,967 --> 00:53:28,843
I'm busy right now,
but I'll be watching you.

777
00:53:28,867 --> 00:53:31,400
Straighten up! You little...

778
00:53:33,133 --> 00:53:35,876
Sure, let's see how this plays out.

779
00:53:35,900 --> 00:53:37,443
Nothing will change by doing that.

780
00:53:37,467 --> 00:53:39,276
Sorry about that. Did you check?

781
00:53:39,300 --> 00:53:41,167
About Ms. Bu Se Mi.

782
00:53:41,867 --> 00:53:43,909
Ugh, yes.

783
00:53:43,933 --> 00:53:45,809
Ugh, thank you.

784
00:53:45,833 --> 00:53:49,343
Her resume's impressive but,

785
00:53:49,367 --> 00:53:52,576
we value character most.

786
00:53:52,600 --> 00:53:55,543
Right? You're the Iseon
Women's University expert.

787
00:53:55,567 --> 00:53:59,576
Principal Lee, I found
one Bu Se Mi graduate.

788
00:53:59,577 --> 00:54:10,227
Officail Website : dramacool.club

789
00:54:10,251 --> 00:54:20,577
Translate by =Qari= @Team Viki

790
00:53:59,600 --> 00:54:01,109
Well,

791
00:54:01,133 --> 00:54:05,909
wouldn't someone like Bu Se Mi
be famous among alumni?

792
00:54:05,933 --> 00:54:10,743
Well, Bu Se Mi I know is much older.

793
00:54:10,767 --> 00:54:12,976
A 94 liner? That's young.

794
00:54:13,000 --> 00:54:17,243
People marry after thirty nowadays.

795
00:54:17,267 --> 00:54:19,909
But Bu Se Mi I know was born in '72.

796
00:54:19,933 --> 00:54:21,009
Fifty-three.

797
00:54:21,033 --> 00:54:23,643
[Iseon Women's University, Bu Se Mi] She has
three kids, and youngest started college.

798
00:54:23,667 --> 00:54:25,576
What?

799
00:54:25,600 --> 00:54:28,476
Well. Check again, okay?

800
00:54:28,500 --> 00:54:30,909
Bu Se Mi isn't a common name, right?

801
00:54:30,933 --> 00:54:33,276
And, you know, my younger
brother? The attorney.

802
00:54:33,300 --> 00:54:35,043
Yeah, Don.

803
00:54:35,067 --> 00:54:39,176
He sent this resume himself.

804
00:54:39,200 --> 00:54:43,109
I have 30 years of alumni records.

805
00:54:43,133 --> 00:54:46,309
Would I miss such a standout graduate?

806
00:54:46,333 --> 00:54:48,767
Did Attorney Lee make a mistake?

807
00:54:49,800 --> 00:54:52,276
That's why we need to verify again.

808
00:54:52,300 --> 00:54:55,700
You can't possibly remember every graduate.

809
00:54:59,500 --> 00:55:04,133
[Teacher Bu Se Mi]

810
00:55:06,967 --> 00:55:09,433
Is he seeing the teacher these days?

811
00:55:12,367 --> 00:55:13,609
Did you see it?

812
00:55:13,633 --> 00:55:16,633
Is there something I
shouldn't see, Attorney?

813
00:55:20,267 --> 00:55:23,567
I'm done eating, so clear this up for me.

814
00:55:41,633 --> 00:55:43,233
Hello?

815
00:55:43,933 --> 00:55:47,543
Yes, Madam. What's the matter?

816
00:55:47,567 --> 00:55:50,176
I think the principal is
investigating my background.

817
00:55:50,200 --> 00:55:51,867
What should I do?

818
00:55:57,500 --> 00:55:59,576
Then do a thorough background check, sis.

819
00:55:59,600 --> 00:56:02,343
People fake degrees and
careers these days, right?

820
00:56:02,367 --> 00:56:07,233
Check her past
workplaces for any incidents.

821
00:56:21,733 --> 00:56:25,276
[Iseon Women's University
Affiliated Kindergarten]

822
00:56:25,300 --> 00:56:26,900
Oh.

823
00:56:30,300 --> 00:56:32,409
32...

824
00:56:32,433 --> 00:56:34,233
Wait, hold on.

825
00:56:42,133 --> 00:56:45,243
Ah, yes. Hello.

826
00:56:45,267 --> 00:56:49,009
That's Iseon Women's University
Kindergarten, right?

827
00:56:49,033 --> 00:56:51,309
We're looking for a
teacher who worked there.

828
00:56:51,333 --> 00:56:54,576
Bu Se Mi, born in 1994.

829
00:56:54,600 --> 00:56:56,843
Ah, one moment.

830
00:56:56,867 --> 00:57:00,567
Born September 13, 1994, correct?

831
00:57:01,367 --> 00:57:03,709
Yes, that's right.

832
00:57:03,733 --> 00:57:06,343
Ah, Ms. Bu Se Mi worked
here until last month.

833
00:57:06,367 --> 00:57:09,576
She's an Iseon Women's
University graduate, right?

834
00:57:09,600 --> 00:57:10,643
Of course, naturally.

835
00:57:10,667 --> 00:57:13,076
We only hire Iseon Women's
University graduates.

836
00:57:13,100 --> 00:57:14,876
Didn't you know?

837
00:57:14,900 --> 00:57:18,667
Ugh, yes. Understood.

838
00:57:20,967 --> 00:57:23,067
Principal.

839
00:57:26,367 --> 00:57:28,576
A million won for just saying a few words?

840
00:57:28,600 --> 00:57:30,543
Ms. Kim, buy something good today.

841
00:57:30,567 --> 00:57:32,567
Ms. Lee, quiet.

842
00:57:58,533 --> 00:58:00,643
Are you going to report me?

843
00:58:00,667 --> 00:58:04,633
Why would I tell you
about that, Ms. Bu Se Mi?

844
00:58:10,933 --> 00:58:12,533
Who are you?

845
00:58:21,333 --> 00:58:23,900
Dong Min! Jeon Dong Min!

846
00:58:27,567 --> 00:58:28,676
Oh my, oh my.

847
00:58:28,700 --> 00:58:30,676
Let go of me.

848
00:58:30,700 --> 00:58:32,576
What on earth are you?

849
00:58:32,600 --> 00:58:35,376
What's your real identity?

850
00:58:35,400 --> 00:58:39,276
Oh my, I'm saying such rude things
at a sacred kindergarten.

851
00:58:39,300 --> 00:58:40,976
Wait, wait.

852
00:58:41,000 --> 00:58:43,309
Dear God, forgive me. Help me.

853
00:58:43,333 --> 00:58:46,700
Oh, don't come closer.

854
00:58:49,967 --> 00:58:52,943
You won't believe anything I say, will you?

855
00:58:52,967 --> 00:58:55,900
What's the story behind these lies? Huh?

856
00:58:57,133 --> 00:58:58,743
By the way,

857
00:58:58,767 --> 00:59:01,943
how did you trick our Don?

858
00:59:01,967 --> 00:59:04,133
Our innocent Don!

859
00:59:06,600 --> 00:59:08,200
Are you two

860
00:59:10,200 --> 00:59:14,476
involved in some way, huh?

861
00:59:14,500 --> 00:59:17,243
That suspicion is quite unpleasant.

862
00:59:17,267 --> 00:59:21,176
What's wrong with our Don?

863
00:59:21,200 --> 00:59:23,276
Oh my.

864
00:59:23,300 --> 00:59:24,609
Oh, what should I do?

865
00:59:24,633 --> 00:59:27,309
[Our Don]

866
00:59:27,333 --> 00:59:28,909
Yes, Attorney. It's me.

867
00:59:28,933 --> 00:59:31,109
Why are you answering my sister's phone?

868
00:59:31,133 --> 00:59:34,143
Don, hey Don, it's your sister.

869
00:59:34,167 --> 00:59:36,876
Oh, silly Don. What should I do?

870
00:59:36,900 --> 00:59:38,876
Sis, calm down first.

871
00:59:38,900 --> 00:59:41,743
Hey, what's going on?

872
00:59:41,767 --> 00:59:45,009
You said you hired someone through
Iseon Kindergarten's principal in Seoul.

873
00:59:45,033 --> 00:59:47,709
Then, why isn't she
an Iseon Women's University graduate?

874
00:59:47,733 --> 00:59:50,976
Who's this person in front of me?

875
00:59:51,000 --> 00:59:53,909
Did you meet at a nightclub? Huh?

876
00:59:53,933 --> 00:59:57,100
Sis, it's not a nightclub
these days, it's a club!

877
00:59:58,133 --> 01:00:00,343
Madam? And sis...

878
01:00:00,367 --> 01:00:02,376
Both of you, calm down first.

879
01:00:02,400 --> 01:00:04,543
Now listen carefully to what I have to say.

880
01:00:04,567 --> 01:00:06,867
Madam? Sis?

881
01:00:08,800 --> 01:00:11,609
Sis, the person beside you now

882
01:00:11,633 --> 01:00:15,433
is the widow of Chairman Ga Sung Ho
of Gaseong Group, who recently passed away.

883
01:00:18,467 --> 01:00:19,776
That gold digger?

884
01:00:19,800 --> 01:00:22,309
- Oh, my.
- Sis, if you say that, that 'gold digger'...

885
01:00:22,333 --> 01:00:26,109
No, Madam will be hurt if she hears that.

886
01:00:26,133 --> 01:00:28,567
I'm not hurt by such things.

887
01:00:29,533 --> 01:00:31,400
Principal Lee Mi Seon.

888
01:00:32,367 --> 01:00:35,176
This kindergarten is facing closure, right?

889
01:00:35,200 --> 01:00:39,467
The landowner could die any day now,
and the kids naturally want to sell, right?

890
01:00:40,800 --> 01:00:42,776
How do you know that?

891
01:00:42,800 --> 01:00:44,567
Three months.

892
01:00:45,767 --> 01:00:47,509
Exactly three months will suffice.

893
01:00:47,533 --> 01:00:50,167
So those three months...

894
01:00:51,367 --> 01:00:52,909
You heard about me, right?

895
01:00:52,933 --> 01:00:55,743
Who I am, how much money I have.

896
01:00:55,767 --> 01:00:57,109
And with that money,

897
01:00:57,133 --> 01:01:00,667
buying this kindergarten's
land would be trivial.

898
01:01:03,000 --> 01:01:05,309
Just give me three months.

899
01:01:05,333 --> 01:01:09,776
If you let me stay here quietly
as a kindergarten teacher,

900
01:01:09,800 --> 01:01:13,500
you'll become the
kindergarten's true owner.

901
01:01:16,167 --> 01:01:17,967
Miss.

902
01:01:19,633 --> 01:01:21,333
Miss.

903
01:01:22,200 --> 01:01:26,667
This must be that famous

904
01:01:27,467 --> 01:01:30,276
noblesse oblige I've heard about.

905
01:01:30,300 --> 01:01:31,843
However, for those three months,

906
01:01:31,867 --> 01:01:34,209
you must absolutely keep it a secret

907
01:01:34,233 --> 01:01:36,276
that I am the widow of Chairman Ga Sung Ho.

908
01:01:36,300 --> 01:01:38,276
During those three months,

909
01:01:38,300 --> 01:01:42,543
everyone will know me only as Ms. Bu
Se Mi from Iseon Women's University.

910
01:01:42,567 --> 01:01:46,200
Of course, Teacher.

911
01:01:47,067 --> 01:01:49,100
- Principal.
- Yes.

912
01:01:53,567 --> 01:01:57,067
Lying itself isn't bad.

913
01:01:58,567 --> 01:02:00,667
As long as you don't get caught.

914
01:02:02,067 --> 01:02:04,667
Of course, Madam.

915
01:02:06,800 --> 01:02:08,433
Principal.

916
01:02:13,667 --> 01:02:15,643
What did you just say?

917
01:02:15,667 --> 01:02:17,300
Huh?

918
01:02:17,933 --> 01:02:19,743
What, Dong Min?

919
01:02:19,767 --> 01:02:21,733
Who is Madam?

920
01:02:26,233 --> 01:02:28,133
You mean Ms. Bu Se Mi?

921
01:02:32,300 --> 01:02:37,967
♫ Starting to be born again ♫

922
01:02:50,533 --> 01:02:53,476
♫ Now is the time ♫

923
01:02:53,500 --> 01:03:01,500
♫ Even hidden scars will shine ♫

924
01:03:01,533 --> 01:03:04,676
♫ I share the light ♫

925
01:03:04,700 --> 01:03:11,509
♫ I'll brighten the days
shrouded in darkness ♫

926
01:03:11,533 --> 01:03:13,476
♫ It's not over ♫

927
01:03:13,500 --> 01:03:21,500
♫ The present isn't bound by the past ♫

928
01:03:21,933 --> 01:03:23,576
♫ Come back to me safely ♫

929
01:03:23,600 --> 01:03:25,500
Back suplex!

930
01:03:27,067 --> 01:03:29,176
You pulled this stunt
all the way from Seoul?

931
01:03:29,200 --> 01:03:30,609
You're crossing the line.

932
01:03:30,633 --> 01:03:32,809
[Muchang Residents' Relationship Chart]
I think the people of Muchang suspect me.

933
01:03:32,833 --> 01:03:35,076
It seems Ga Seon Yeong filed
a missing person's report.

934
01:03:35,100 --> 01:03:36,909
Ms. Bu Se Mi.

935
01:03:36,933 --> 01:03:38,843
Wait a second, Miss!

936
01:03:38,867 --> 01:03:40,443
If someone comes looking for me,
pretend you don't know me.

937
01:03:40,467 --> 01:03:41,476
Don't you trust me?

938
01:03:41,500 --> 01:03:43,743
I'm just telling you to be careful.

939
01:03:43,767 --> 01:03:45,480
Is that ordinary info?

940
01:03:45,504 --> 01:03:47,409
[Iseon Kindergarten]
It's worth hundreds of millions.

941
01:03:47,433 --> 01:03:49,009
Friend.

942
01:03:49,033 --> 01:03:50,867
Found you.
